    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-12T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-12T08:00:00-05:00" n="604"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/1326: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-12T16:00:00+03:00"
                            >March 12, 1943—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received March 12—3:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>150. The Soviet press of March 12 gave wide coverage to Tass despatches from the
                    United States press [of] Stettinius’ statement of March 7 regarding Lend-Lease
                    supplies to Russia<note n="80" xml:id="d604fn80">See the <hi rend="italic">New
                            York Times</hi>, March 8, 1943, p. 19; for complete text, see the <hi
                            rend="italic">Congressional Record</hi>, vol. 89, pt. 2, p. 1700. See
                        also the Eighth Quarterly Report to Congress (Washington, Government
                        Printing Office, 1943), summary of which is printed in Department of State
                            <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, March 20, 1943, p. 230.</note> was
                    carried in considerable detail and included many figures on supplies sent up to
                    February 1.</p>
                <p>Stettinius’ recent radio speech on the necessity of creating an army of 8,200,000
                    was published at some length as well as the Vice President’s recent address in
                        Columbus.<note n="81" xml:id="d604fn81">Address delivered at Columbus, Ohio,
                        on March 8, 1943; for text, see <hi rend="italic">Congressional Record</hi>,
                        vol. 89, pt. 9, p. A1087.</note> No reference to the Soviet Union was
                    contained in the Tass version of Wallace’s speech.</p>
                <p>The passage of the Lend-Lease Bill in the House of Representatives<note n="82"
                        xml:id="d604fn82">The House passed the Lend-Lease extension act on March 10,
                        1943, followed by the Senate on March 11. Upon President Roosevelt’s
                        signature the same day it became law; 57 Stat. 20.</note> was also
                    prominently carried.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Standley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
